\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Fink Binary Distribution ReadMe
\f0\b0\fs28 \
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
This is the installer package for Fink IN_VERSION. Fink is a distribution of Open Source Unix software ported to Mac OS X. Open Source software is developed by volunteers from all over the world, available for free and with complete source code.\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Important Installer Notes:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx420\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\li420\fi-280\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \'a5	Do not use this installer to update existing Fink installations. To update, see\
     \ul http://fink.sourceforge.net/download/upgrade.php\ulnone \
\'a5	This version of fink requires Mac OS X 10.3. For other versions of Mac OS X, see the Fink web site.  \
\'a5	Don\'d5t trust the \'d2disk space required\'d3 figures.\
\'a5	For installation on a separate volume, see below.\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
Apart from that, the installer is pretty safe to use. It will not touch your system files or in fact anything outside the /sw directory.\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Configuration
\f0\b0 \
During the installation, your shell's configuration files will be examined, and if a change is needed (such as during a first-time installation), you will be presented with a dialog window asking for permission to alter these files.  If anything goes wrong during this process, you can try again by launching 
\f2\b\fs26 pathsetup 
\f0\b0\fs28 application which appears on the installer disk, or by running (from the command line in a Terminal.app window)\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\li420\ql\qnatural

\f2\b\fs16 \cf0 \

\fs26 /sw/bin/pathsetup.sh <RETURN>
\fs16 \
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f0\b0\fs28 \cf0 (This step should also be repeated by any other users on your system: each user must either run the  
\f2\b\fs26 pathsetup
\f0\b0\fs28  application, or the  
\f2\b\fs26 /sw/bin/pathsetup.sh
\f0\b0\fs28  command in his or her own account, in order to use Fink.)\
\
If the 
\f2\b\fs26 pathsetup 
\f0\b0\fs28 application generates error messages, consult the documentation, particularly section 2.3 "Setting Up Your Environment" of the User's Guide.\
\
More detailed instructions can be found in Documentation.html and FAQ.html provided on the Fink IN_VERSION Installer disk.  The same information (and more) can be found on the Fink website:\
