\f1\b \cf0 Getting more packages
\f0\b0 \
This installer serves only as a starting point. The Fink distribution uses its own package system built around dpkg. dpkg is a sophisticated package manager that was written for and by the Debian GNU/Linux project and has been ported to Mac OS X. When this installer is done, you can use various package management tools to download and install more packages. You have several choices:\
\
\pard\tx420\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\li420\fi-280\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \'a5	
\f1\b FinkCommander
\f0\b0  - a GUI for fink, available in the FinkCommander folder of the Fink IN_VERSION Installer  disk, or at \
         \ul http://finkcommander.sourceforge.net/\
\ulnone    To install FinkCommander, simply drag it to your hard disk. \
\'a5	
\f1\b apt-get
\f0\b0  - a command line utility that is able to download binary packages from the Internet. (A ported Debian tool.)\
\'a5	
\f1\b dselect
\f0\b0  - a friendly front-end to apt-get. It allows you to browse through the list of available packages and select which ones you want to install. (Also a ported Debian tool.)\
\'a5	
\f1\b fink
\f0\b0  - a command line utility that downloads source code and compiles it on your machine. Some packages are not available as binary packages, so you must use the fink command to get them. You will need the Developer Tools to compile software on your machine.\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
These tools require administrative privileges, like this installer. On the command line, prefix the command with \'d4sudo\'d5. When asked, enter the password for your normal user account. The fink command is set up to use sudo automatically when needed.\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Installation on an Alternate Volume\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f0\b0 \cf0 You can install fink on a separate volume. Fink will create a symlink /sw that points to the /sw directory on the volume you choose. You may copy the fink tree somewhere else, but make sure /sw always points to the fink root. If you wish to install fink with a non-/sw prefix, do not use this installer. You need to use the separate tar.gz installer from the web site. (and binary packages will not be available)\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f1\b \cf0 Troubleshooting an installation\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

\f0\b0 \cf0 There are a few situations known to cause trouble for installing Fink.  These situations are now quite rare, since the software causing conflicts is quite old and has been updated.\
\pard\tx420\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\li420\fi-280\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \'a5	You cannot use this installer if you have old versions of MacGIMP or OpenOSX.com\'d5s GIMP package installed.\
\'a5	You cannot use this installer if you have Virex 7.2 installed.  (MacAfee has released an update, Virex 7.2.1, which addresses the problem with the previous version.)\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural
\cf0 In both of these cases, the third-party software erroneously creates an /sw directory which conflicts with Fink's.\
\
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\tx7200\ql\qnatural

